headline.main: Philippines Says Condemns Extrajudicial Killings, but None During Drugs War
headline.print_headline: Philippines Says Condemns Extrajudicial Killings, but None During Drugs War

lead_paragraph: The Philippines on Saturday said it was committed to human rights and condemned extrajudicial killings but said those were "not to be confused" with incidents in its war on drugs, after a U.S. State Department report voiced concern about such deaths.
